03898nam a22006735i 9788395793806DE-B159720210927121507.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210927t20202020pl     fo  d z      eng d  a97883957938067 a10.2478/97883957938062doi  a(DE-B1597)563365  a(OCoLC)1202623543  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aplcPL 7aBUS0810002bisacsh1 aVasenska, Ivanka, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aSmart Analysis of Tourism Policy Efficiency in Bulgaria for the Period 1980-2017 /cIvanka Vasenska, Ani Stoykova, Mariya Paskaleva. 1aWarsaw ;aBerlin : bSciendo, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (82 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tINTRODUCTION -- tCHAPTER ONE: The history of the Bulgarian tourism industry and its trends -- tCHAPTER TWO: EMPIRICAL COMPARISON OF BULGARIAN TOURISM FOR THE PERIOD 1980-2017 -- tCONCLUSION -- tREFERENCES -- tAppendix 1. The dynamics of the variables for the first period (1980- 1989) -- tAppendix 2. The dynamics of the variables for the second period (1990- 2017)0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe purpose of this study is to determine the role of tourism in the economy of Bulgaria. In this paper, we present the history of the Bulgarian tourism industry trends from the beginning to its contemporary policy patterns. We apply an econometric methodology consisting of unit root test, cointegration analysis, linear regression, correlation analysis, Granger causality test and 3-D visualizations by IBM Watson Studio based on the statistics for the period 1980-2017. Exploring the link between tourism and the economic development of Bulgaria, the tourism – led - growth hypothesis about Bulgaria is validated for the post-communism period. Our findings show that a relationship between tourism and Bulgaria’s economic development exists. We can conclude that tourism is in part an endogenous growth process. ABSTRACTING & INDEXING Smart Analysis of Tourism Policy Efficiency in Bulgaria for the Period 1980-2017 is covered by the following services: Baidu Scholar EBSCO Discovery Service Google Books Google Scholar J-Gate Naviga (Softweco) Primo Central (ExLibris) ReadCube Summon (ProQuest) TDOne (TDNet) WorldCat (OCLC)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh1 aPaskaleva, Mariya, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStoykova, Ani, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cEPUBz97883957938130 cprintz978839577139240uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9788395793806423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9788395793806/original  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK